        <h1 class="page-heading container">
          
          
        </h1>
      </div>
      
  <div class="container">
    
    
      
      
      <div class="hansard-meta">
        
          <div class="document-thumbnail">
            <a href="/media/hansards/national_assembly/13th/documents/2026/na-2026-02-19-afternoon.pdf" target="_blank">
              
              
                <img src="/media/hansards/national_assembly/13th/thumbnails/2026/na-2026-02-19-afternoon.webp"
                     alt="Document thumbnail" width="" height="">
              
              <p class="view-doc">Click to view PDF</p>
            </a>
          </div>
        
        <div class="head-metadata">
          <span class="house">
            <strong>House:</strong>
            
              National Assembly
            
          </span>
          <span class="day">
            <strong>Day:</strong> Thursday
          </span>
          
            <span class="session">
              <strong>Session:</strong> Afternoon Sitting
            
          </span>
          <span class="time">
            <strong>Time:</strong> 2:30 PM
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="sentiment-data">
          <div class="doc-summary">
            <h3>Hansard Summary</h3>
            The afternoon sitting opened with Hon. Millie Odhiambo-Mabona raising a point of order over alleged misstatements about funding, prompting a brief exchange on minority representation and parliamentary conduct. The Deputy Speaker welcomed students from Nyandarua National Polytechnic, after which the House moved on to a series of technical amendments to a Bill, overseen by the Temporary Chairman.

Members highlighted several governance concerns, including KNEC&#x27;s handling of exam candidates, alleged illegal occupation of public utility land in Embakasi West, and the absence of NTSA services in Turkana County. They repeatedly noted the non‑attendance of departmental committee chairs and sought formal statements, with some commitments given for follow‑up within two weeks.

Members of Parliament paid tribute to retiring staff Florence Abonyo, lauding her 34‑35 years of dedicated service, humility and mentorship to new members. The speakers highlighted her impact on parliamentary operations, the importance of recognizing long‑term civil servants, and praised the culture of appreciation within the House.
            <h4 class="doc-sentiment">Sentimental Analysis</h4>
            Mixed
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <hr>
      <header class="hansard-header">
        <h1 class="parliament-title">THE PARLIAMENT OF KENYA</h1>
        
          <h1 class="house-title">NATIONAL ASSEMBLY</h1>
        
        <h1 class="document-title">THE HANSARD</h1>
      </header>
      
        <div class="hansard-content">
          
          <!-- Display content chunks preserving original CSS classes -->
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710869" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="speech-content"><p>Thursday, 19th February 2026</p></div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710870" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="scene-description">[The Speaker (Hon. Moses Wetang’ula) in the Chair]</div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710871" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="contributor-name">Hon. Speaker</div><div class="speech-content">
<p>Serjeant-at-Arms, ring the Quorum Bell. Hon. Millie, where are your people.</p>
<aside class="procedural-note">(The Quorum Bell was rung)</aside>
<p>Hon. Members, we now have quorum to transact business. Clerk-at-the-Table, I have a Communication, but I will come to it later. Go to the next Order.</p>
<p>Hon. Murugara, are you holding brief for the Leader of the Majority Party?</p>
</div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710872" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="contributor-name"><a href="/mps-performance/national-assembly/13th-parliament/george-gitonga-murugara/">Hon. George Murugara (Tharaka, UDA)</a></div><div class="speech-content">
<p>Yes, I am. Hon. Speaker, on behalf of the Leader of the Majority Party, I beg to lay the following Papers on the Table:</p>
</div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710873" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="contributor-name">Hon. Speaker</div><div class="speech-content">
<p>Leader of the Delegation to New York, Hon. Wamuchomba.</p>
</div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710874" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="contributor-name"><a href="/mps-performance/national-assembly/13th-parliament/gathoni-wamuchomba/">Hon. Gathoni Wamuchomba (Githunguri, UDA)</a></div><div class="speech-content">
<p>Hon. Speaker, I beg to lay the following Paper on the Table:</p>
</div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710875" class="chunk-wrapper"><h2 class="header-section">Report of the Parliament of Kenya Delegation to the 67th Session of the</h2></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710876" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="contributor-name">Hon. Speaker</div><div class="speech-content">
<p>Thank you, Hon. Wamuchomba. Hon. Rahab Mukami, Leader of the Delegation to the Pan-African Parliamentary (PAP) .</p>
</div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710877" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="contributor-name"><a href="/mps-performance/national-assembly/13th-parliament/rahab-mukami-wachira/">Hon. Rahab Mukami (Nyeri County, UDA)</a></div><div class="speech-content">
<p>Hon. Speaker, I beg to lay the following Paper on the Table:</p>
</div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710878" class="chunk-wrapper"><h2 class="header-section">Report of the Kenya Delegation to the 3rd Ordinary Session of the Sixth</h2></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710879" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="contributor-name">Hon. Speaker</div><div class="speech-content">
<p>Hon. Peter Kihungi, Leader of Interfaith Delegation to Marrakech.</p>
</div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710880" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="contributor-name"><a href="/mps-performance/national-assembly/13th-parliament/peter-irungu-kihungi/">Hon. Peter Kihungi (Kangema, UDA)</a></div><div class="speech-content">
<p>Hon. Speaker, give me some time. I have not been given the right report.</p>
</div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710881" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="contributor-name">Hon. Speaker</div><div class="speech-content">
<p>You cannot be given the right report. You should have the report. Why is your report listed on the Order Paper?</p>
</div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710882" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="contributor-name"><a href="/mps-performance/national-assembly/13th-parliament/peter-irungu-kihungi/">Hon. Peter Kihungi (Kangema, UDA)</a></div><div class="speech-content">
<p>Let me take it from the Table.</p>
</div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710883" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="contributor-name">Hon. Speaker</div><div class="speech-content">
<p>Okay. Chairperson, Public Accounts Committee. Hon. Tindi Mwale.</p>
</div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710884" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="contributor-name"><a href="/mps-performance/national-assembly/13th-parliament/nicholas-scott-tindi-mwale/">Hon. Nicholas Mwale (Butere, ODM)</a></div><div class="speech-content">
<p>Hon. Speaker, I beg to lay the following paper on the Table:</p>
</div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710885" class="chunk-wrapper"><h2 class="header-section">Report of the Public Accounts Committee on the Examination of Audited</h2></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710886" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="page-break"><div class="date-line">19th February 2026 NATIONAL ASSEMBLY DEBATES<span class="page-number"> 2</span></div></div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710887" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="contributor-name">Hon. Speaker</div><div class="speech-content">
<p>Chairperson, Departmental Committee on Transport and Infrastructure, Hon. GK.</p>
</div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710888" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="contributor-name"><a href="/mps-performance/national-assembly/13th-parliament/komingoi-kibet-kirui/">Hon. Kibet Komingoi (Bureti, UDA)</a></div><div class="speech-content">
<p>Hon. Speaker, I am here on behalf of the Chairman.</p>
<p>Hon. Speaker, I beg to lay the following Paper on the Table: Report of the Departmental Committee on Transport and Infrastructure on its Consideration of Sessional Paper No.6 of 2024 on the National Aviation Policy. Thank you.</p>
</div></div>
          
            <!-- Preserve original HTML structure and CSS classes -->
            <div id="chunk-710889" class="chunk-wrapper"><div class="contributor-name">Hon. Speaker</div><div class="speech-content">
<p>Thank you. Hon. Kihungi, are you ready now? We stay it to Tuesday. Put your house in order.</p>
